[SN]TITLE[SN]
Met Office heavy rain warning for south Wales

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A yellow "be aware" warning for heavy rain is in place in south Wales throughout Saturday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Met Office warning is in place between 02:00 BST and 18:00, when conditions are expected to clear.
It said showers on Friday evening would become more frequent overnight, be often heavy with a risk of hail, lightning and gusty winds.
It warned of localised surface water flooding and difficult driving conditions.
